LAFIA – Justice Sidi Bege, the Emir of Lafia, has on Tuesday charged practicing journalists in Nasarawa State to imbibe the spirit of developmental journalism for the development of the state and country. The monarch stated this while playing host to leadership Correspondents’ Chapel of Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), Nasarawa State chapter, who paid him courtesy visit in his palace in Lafia, the state capital. He said journalists were critical stakeholders that their service could not be undermined in the state and in the country. The Emir, who was happy over the visit, said the journalists in Nasarawa State should try and report the state in positively light. According to Justice Bage, “Try all you can and help us. The country is passing through a very difficult reality at moment, no doubt about that.